ftp://korea.stanford.edu/pub/Hangul/CodeConv/hcode2.0.6.tar.gz and several
archives in Korea including ftp://ftp.kaist.ac.kr) which can convert 
Romanized Hangul to and from KSC 5601 and a few other Hangul codes. Hangul 
Romanization code used in hcode is one agreed upon by both Koreas
(South and North) and submitted to ISO back in 1992, but that's 
quite different from what you usually expect. If you wish to learn 
Korea seriously, I wouldn't recommend you use Romanized input method 
even if there's a program with support for it. 

