Hangul font (300 dpi pk or metafont) takes 10-15MB. How large
would it be if all of 11172 syllables in the new
Korean standard KSC 5700 were defined that way(
syllable by syllable)? As you may have already heard, 
KSC 5601 would be faded out gradually as KSC 5700, 
announced as the new Korean standard in late last year, 
takes over. Wansung encoding seems to have 
an advantage of much faster bitmap (pk) generation
from metafont over previous encoding(Wansung-Johab
mixed ?).( I wonder why it takes so long(tens of days)
