I don't know if I understood your question correctly for
I am in no way a computer programmer, but I can say we 
don't type in Hanja directly from keyboard -- i.e. there 
is no key(s) or key-combination(s) for them. What we do, 
instead, is type in the Korean character as we read the 
Hanja. Of course that Korean character can correspond to 
more than one Hanja, so we need a program with which we 
can select the appropriate Hanja character.

And, about the pronunciation key: this is, I think, rather
in primitive form. I think the Hanja data is indexed by
each Hanja's Korean pronunciation(i.e. Korean character).
Which, in turn, means Hanja itself is not assigned to 
any pronunciation. 

