   각(11): 刻, 却, 各, 恪, 慤, 殼, 珏, 脚, 覺, 角, 閣,
   ...


[가] is 0xb0a1. I hope that you already have its pronounciation
such as [KA]. The number (29) tells that there are 29 hanja characters
sharing identical pronounciation. With this algorithm, every
hanja characters can be automatically translated into corresponding
hangul characters. A hanja with multiple pronounciation method according
to its semantics appears multiple places following its pronounciation.
The example is given below. Please note that [설] and [세] for <說> are
different hangul characters(or readings).

    설(13): 卨, 屑, 楔, 泄, 洩, 渫, 舌, 薛, 褻, 設, <說>, 雪, 齧,
    세(9): 醒, 世, 勢, 歲, 洗, 稅, 笹, 細, <說>,

